import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d
%matplotlib inline

# 
# mu : 
# sigma :  
def gauss(x, mu, sigma):
    N, D = x.shape
    c1 = 1 / (2 * np.pi)**(D / 2)
    c2 = 1 / (np.linalg.det(sigma)**(1 / 2))
    inv_sigma = np.linalg.inv(sigma)
    c3 = x - mu
    c4 = np.dot(c3, inv_sigma)
    c5 = np.zeros(N)
    for d in range(D):
        c5 = c5 + c4[:, d] * c3[:, d]
    p = c1 * c2 * np.exp(-c5 / 2)
    return p

$\mu=[1,2]^T$, $\Sigma=\begin{bmatrix}1 & 0\\0 & 1\end{bmatrix}$2 $\boldsymbol{x}=[1,2]^T, \quad [2,1]^T,\quad [3,4]^T$

In[80]:
def show_contour_gauss(mu, sig, x0_range0, x1_range1):
    xn = 40  # 
    x0 = np.linspace(x0_range[0], x0_range[1], xn)
    x1 = np.linspace(x1_range[0], x1_range[1], xn)
    xx0, xx1 = np.meshgrid(x0, x1)
    x = np.c_[xx0.ravel(), xx1.ravel()]
    f = gauss(x, mu, sig)
    f = f.reshape(xx0.shape)
    f = f.T
    cont = plt.contour(xx0, xx1, f, 15, colors='k')
    plt.grid(True)

In[81]:
def show3d_gauss(ax, mu, sig, x0_range, x1_range):
    xn = 40  # 
    x0 = np.linspace(x0_range[0], x0_range[1], xn)
    x1 = np.linspace(x1_range[0], x1_range[1], xn)
    xx0, xx1 = np.meshgrid(x0, x1)
    x = np.c_[xx0.ravel(), xx1.ravel()]
    f = gauss(x, mu, sig)
    f = f.reshape(xx0.shape)
    f = f.T
    ax.plot_surface(xx0, xx1, f, 
                    rstride=2, cstride=2, alpha=0.3, 
                    color='blue', edgecolor='black')
In[82]:
# 
Fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(15, 6))
x0_range=[-4, 6]
x1_range=[-4, 6]

Fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1)
show_contour_gauss(mu, sigma, x0_range, x1_range)
plt.xlim(x0_range)
plt.ylim(x1_range)
plt.xlabel('$x_0$', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('$x_1$', fontsize=14)

Ax = Fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection='3d')
show3d_gauss(Ax, mu, sigma, x0_range, x1_range)
Ax.set_zticks([0.05, 0.10])
Ax.set_xlabel('$x_0$', fontsize=14)
Ax.set_ylabel('$x_1$', fontsize=14)
Ax.view_init(30, -120)
plt.show()
